Citation.sTitle: Viscosities and refractive indices of binary mixtures of 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate and 1-butyl-2,3-dimethylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate with water at 298 K
Citation.sAbstract: Viscosities and refractive indices have been determined for (water + 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate) and (water + 1- butyl-2,3-dimethylimidazolium tetrafluoroborate) mixtures at 298.15 K, over the whole composition range. The refractive indices were compared with the predictions of the Lorentz Lorenz, Wiener, and Gladstone Dale equations. Viscosity deviations (Dg) and refractive index deviations (DnD) have been calculated and fitted to the Redlich Kister polynomial equations. DnD are positive whereas Dg are negative over the entire mixture composition for the two salts. The influence of the structure of imidazolium cation on the above physicochemical properties was discussed.
